J. Gunnell Law, LLC — Website

This repository contains the Next.js site for J. Gunnell Law, LLC. It uses the App Router, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS, with API routes for contact and SMS consent and optional Supabase persistence (see `supabase/` and `.env.example`).

Stack

- Next.js
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- App Router

Project Structure

```text
.
├── public/
│   └── images/              # Static assets used by Next.js
├── src/
│   ├── app/                 # App Router routes and global styles
│   ├── components/          # Reusable site sections and shared UI
│   ├── content/             # Page-specific copy and structured content
│   └── lib/
│       ├── metadata.ts      # Shared metadata helper
│       └── siteConfig.ts    # Reusable firm/contact/site configuration
├── package.json
└── README
```

Routes

- `/`
- `/about`
- `/contact`
- `/privacy`
- `/terms`

Content Management

All repeated firm data lives in `src/lib/siteConfig.ts`, including:

- Firm and attorney names
- Titles
- Phone and email
- Address details
- Navigation and legal footer links
- Shared consultation text and disclaimers

Page-specific content lives in `src/content/`.

Local Development

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Start the development server:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Build for production:

```bash
npm run build
```

Design Notes

- The site keeps a clear law-firm visual direction with Tailwind.
- Reusable sections are componentized for extension.

